<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1034,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1370,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[325,623,1370,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. &amp; McHugh, J. V. (2002) Revision of Acrophotopsis (Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalminae), with a new species from Baja California. Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 11, 363 - 374." type="journal article" year="2002">
Pitts and McHugh (
<number box="[553,615,1370,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reviewed this genus. Recent morphological studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. &amp; McHugh, J. V. (2002) Revision of Acrophotopsis (Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalminae), with a new species from Baja California. Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 11, 363 - 374." type="journal article" year="2002">
Pitts &amp; McHugh 
<number box="[151,213,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[225,346,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. (2003) Schusterphotopsis, a new genus of Sphaeropthalmini (Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalminae) from California, with notes on the closely related genera Acrophotopsis Schuster and Dilophotopsis Schuster clade. Zootaxa, 333, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2003">
Pitts 
<number box="[284,346,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson" box="[358,599,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Wilson, J. S. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2008) Revision of velvet ant genus Dilophotopsis Schuster (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) by using molecular and morphological data, with implications for desert biogeography. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 101, 514 - 524." type="journal article" year="2008">
Wilson &amp; Pitts 
<number box="[537,599,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Pitts &amp; Wilson 
<number box="[791,851,1408,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2009.0">2009</number>
) all concurred in suggesting that 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1409,1408,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Acrophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1409,1408,1433]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Acrophotopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[370,541,1445,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dilophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[370,541,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dilophotopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on morphology; this conclusion has been confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P., Wilson, J. S. &amp; von Dohlen, C. D. (2010) Recent radiation in the Nearctic nocturnal Sphaeropthalmini velvet ants (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) driven by Neogene Orogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 56, 134 - 145." type="journal article">
Pitts 
<emphasis box="[1374,1429,1445,1470]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[159,224,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Along with many characters shared by the males (
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[841,966,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. (2003) Schusterphotopsis, a new genus of Sphaeropthalmini (Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalminae) from California, with notes on the closely related genera Acrophotopsis Schuster and Dilophotopsis Schuster clade. Zootaxa, 333, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="2003">
Pitts 
<number box="[903,966,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[978,1246,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. &amp; McHugh, J. V. (2002) Revision of Acrophotopsis (Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalminae), with a new species from Baja California. Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 11, 363 - 374." type="journal article" year="2002">
Pitts &amp; McHugh 
<number box="[1183,1246,1482,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the females of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,321,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Acrophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,321,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Acrophotopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[379,544,1520,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Dilophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[379,544,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dilophotopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are morphologically very similar, sharing several notable characters of the mandibles and pygidium. In addition, the females of these genera share many characteristics with females of the 
<taxonomicName box="[194,477,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orestes">
<emphasis box="[194,477,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Sphaeropthalma orestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (Pitts &amp; Wilson 
<number box="[846,909,1594,1620]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), a relationship also confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="3" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P., Wilson, J. S. &amp; von Dohlen, C. D. (2010) Recent radiation in the Nearctic nocturnal Sphaeropthalmini velvet ants (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) driven by Neogene Orogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 56, 134 - 145." type="journal article">
Pitts 
<emphasis box="[1377,1428,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[159,224,1632,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
